      "name": "destructive-confirm",
      "type": "registry:block",
      "title": "Destructive confirm",
      "description": "The default destructive confirm — one AlertDialog with Cancel / Delete, then a post-commit toast.",
      "registryDependencies": [
        "alert-dialog",
        "button",
        "card",
        "sidebar",
        "sonner"
      ],
      "meta": {
        "sfabKind": "block",
        "iframeHeight": 720
      },
      "docs": "The baseline for ordinary destroys: a single AlertDialog with Cancel /\nDelete. Run the mutation in the action's `onClick`, then confirm with a\ntoast. Escalate to `type-to-confirm` only for irreversible, org-scoped\ndeletes. Mount one `<Toaster />` at the shell for the post-commit toast.",
